[Course_Description]
Adobe FrameMaker—a documentation tool for authoring and publishing technical content—can help make the task of generating complex documents a bit easier. In this course, learn how to get started with the 2017 release of this popular software. David Rivers explains how to add and format text, customize page layouts to suit your needs, and work with colors, character formats, and graphics. He also covers editing documents, working with tables, using footnotes and cross-references, generating books and indexes, and using conditional text and hyperlinks.